{"image_id": "ATO_2018_page_100", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "ATMOS ENERGY CORPORATION", "bbox": [470.4, 158.9, 804.7, 179.7]}, {"text": "NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS — (Continued)", "bbox": [292.9, 196.4, 981.9, 217.2]}, {"text": "At September 30, 2018 and 2017, the Plan held 716,700 shares of our common stock which represented", "bbox": [204.2, 246.6, 1070.0, 267.4]}, {"text": "12.7 percent and 11.8 percent of total Plan assets. These shares generated dividend income for the Plan of", "bbox": [162.5, 271.6, 1044.5, 292.4]}, {"text": "approximately $1.4 million and $1.7 million during fiscal 2018 and 2017.", "bbox": [162.5, 296.6, 777.5, 317.4]}, {"text": "Our employee pension plan expenses and liabilities are determined on an actuarial basis and are affected by", "bbox": [204.2, 334.1, 1102.7, 354.9]}, {"text": "numerous assumptions and estimates including the market value of plan assets, estimates of the expected return", "bbox": [162.5, 359.1, 1093.6, 379.9]}, {"text": "on plan assets and assumed discount rates and demographic data. We review the estimates and assumptions", "bbox": [162.5, 384.1, 1059.6, 404.9]}, {"text": "underlying our employee pension plans annually based upon a September 30 measurement date. The develop-", "bbox": [162.5, 409.1, 1080.8, 429.9]}, {"text": "ment of our assumptions is fully described in our significant accounting policies in Note 2. The actuarial assump-", "bbox": [162.5, 434.1, 1109.9, 454.9]}, {"text": "tions used to determine the pension liability for the Plan was determined as of September 30, 2018 and 2017 and", "bbox": [162.5, 459.1, 1102.6, 479.9]}, {"text": "the actuarial assumptions used to determine the net periodic pension cost for the Plan was determined as of Sep-", "bbox": [162.5, 484.1, 1099.3, 504.9]}, {"text": "tember 30, 2017, 2016 and 2015. On October 23, 2018, the Society of Actuaries released its annually-updated", "bbox": [162.5, 509.1, 1079.3, 529.9]}, {"text": "mortality i